title: Wissahickon Cross
course: 3km of East Coast Grass with some gravel roadways and a sandy section. It has one-set of 40cm high planks spaced 4m apart and one grass run-up. It has one double pit located roughly halfway around the track.
registration: Registration will be available online at www.bikereg.com or on the day-of the event.
notes: This is a UCI Class 2 event and will be held under UCI regulations. UCI scale of penalties will apply. The Elite Men, Elite Women, Master Women 35+ and U23 Men must have a UCI license.  A domestic USCF or NORBA license is acceptable for all other categories.
directions: From the Pennsylvania Turnpike Exit # 312:  Take Route 100 North for approximately 4 miles, cross Route 401. The race is 0.3 miles further North on the left.
